ch3rryflower - v1.3b4 by @dora2_yuruyi
iPhone 4 only

#How to use  

0) change directory to ch3rryflower (ver, X.X) via terminal
*Launch terminal and change directory to ch3rryflower_vX.X/macos ("cd" command).
cd ch3rryflower_vX.X/macos

1) make iBoot
Create a patched iBoot.
[USE_SCRIPT]
./make_iBoot.sh <ipsw> -iv [iv] -k [key]

2) make CFW
./cherry <ipsw> custom.ipsw -bbupdate -memory -derebusantiquis <base-ipsw> iBoot
base-ipsw is required for iBoot exploits. Select the version with SHSH and the presence of De Rebus Antiquis. (iOS 7.1.2 FW)

if you selected ios 4, The following modification need to be made:
./ios4fix custom.ipsw -t ios4original.ipsw iPhone3,1_7.1.2_11D257_Restore.ipsw

3) Restore  
First, put in device to dfu mode.
Then put into pwned dfu mode.

./pwnedDFU -p

It will then receive iOS 7.1.2 SHSH and restore iOS 6.1.3 CFW.

--- command start ---
./idevicerestore -t iPhone3,1_7.1.2_11D257_Restore.ipsw
mv -v shsh/{ecid}-{device}-7.1.2.shsh shsh/{ecid}-{device}-6.1.3.shsh
./idevicerestore -e -w iPhone3,1_6.1.3_10B329_Custom.ipsw
--- command end ---

(X) Remove iBoot exploit
put in device to dfu mode.

--- command start ---
cd remove
./disable
--- command end ---


ver. 1.2.2 [5]
Update: 2019-10-21
